  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "The old file had a torn page and faded ink, but the important line was still easy enough to read.",
      "zh": "那份舊資料有一頁破損、墨水也褪色了，但重要的那一行字還是看得清楚。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"People don't keep paper records like this anymore,\" the secretary said, closing the drawer carefully.",
      "zh": "秘書小心地關上抽屜說：「現在已經沒有人這樣保存紙本紀錄了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The school secretary looked a little surprised to see them again so soon.",
      "zh": "學校秘書看到他們這麼快又出現，看起來有點意外。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"The fourth floor stairs?\" she said. \"That's a new one. Let me check.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「四樓樓梯？這個我倒是第一次聽人來問，我查查看。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "She pulled out an even older stack of papers than before, soft and a little yellow at the edges.",
      "zh": "她拿出了一疊比上次還要更舊的紙，邊角又軟又有點泛黃。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Here it is,\" she said. \"Fourteen years ago, one step on that staircase was damaged.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「找到了，十四年前，那座樓梯有一個階梯壞了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"A student stepped on it and fell. Not badly hurt, but scared enough to tell everyone.\"",
      "zh": "「一個學生踩到那裡跌倒了，傷得不重，但嚇得跟大家講了這件事。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"The school fixed the step within a week,\" the secretary said. \"It was never a problem again.\"",
      "zh": "秘書說：「學校一個星期內就把階梯修好了，之後再也沒出過問題。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco looked up. \"A week? But people still avoid those stairs today.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 抬起頭：「一個星期？但現在大家還是避開那座樓梯。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"The step was fixed,\" the secretary said, \"but the story wasn't.\"",
      "zh": "秘書說：「階梯修好了，但故事沒有跟著修好。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "She explained that the student who fell told younger students. Those students told the next class after them.",
      "zh": "她解釋，跌倒的那個學生把這件事告訴了學弟妹，那些學生又告訴了下一屆的同學。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Each time the story was told, a small piece changed: the year, the time of day, how badly someone got hurt.",
      "zh": "每講一次，故事就會有一小部分跟著變：年份、時間、受傷的程度。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"By now,\" the secretary said, \"almost nobody knows the real step was fixed fourteen years ago.\"",
      "zh": "秘書說：「到現在，幾乎沒有人知道那個真正的階梯十四年前就修好了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice sat back in her chair. \"So we're not looking for something broken,\" she said. \"We're looking for a story that never got the news.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 靠著椅背坐下：「所以我們不是在找一個壞掉的東西，」她說：「我們是在找一個從來沒有收到消息的故事。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco smiled at that sentence and wrote it down word for word.",
      "zh": "Coco 對這句話笑了笑，一字不改地把它寫了下來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "That afternoon, they walked the fourth floor stairs together, step by step, all the way up.",
      "zh": "那天下午，他們一起一階一階走上四樓的樓梯，一路走到頂。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Nothing sounded strange. Nothing moved. It felt exactly like every other staircase in the school.",
      "zh": "沒有任何奇怪的聲音，什麼都沒有晃動，感覺就跟學校裡任何一座樓梯一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Fourteen years is a long time to be afraid of nothing,\" Bernice said.",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「為了什麼都沒有的事害怕十四年，真的太久了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"It's not nothing,\" Coco said. \"It's a good story. Good stories are hard to stop.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「不是什麼都沒有，這是一個好故事，好故事很難停下來。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "That gave them an idea for their next episode: not just telling the truth, but explaining why the wrong story lasted so long.",
      "zh": "這給了他們下一集的靈感：不只是說出真相，還要解釋為什麼錯的故事能流傳這麼久。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan, hearing their plan, added one more idea. \"Maybe end the episode by walking the stairs live, on the recording.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師聽到他們的計畫，補充了一個點子：「或許可以在錄音的時候，直接走一次樓梯給大家聽。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice smiled at the idea immediately.",
      "zh": "Bernice 立刻對這個點子露出笑容。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Fourteen steps, fourteen years,\" she said. \"That sounds like a good line for the show.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「十四階，十四年，這句話當節目台詞很不錯。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco laughed and added the number to her notes, just in case it turned out to matter later.",
      "zh": "Coco 笑了，把這個數字也記進筆記裡，以防之後真的用得上。"
    }
  ],
